<TEXT>
labor party leader shimon peres won a 
parliamentary showdown with the rival likud bloc today when 
lawmakers voted noconfidence in prime minister yitzhak shamirs 
hardline government 
the 6055 vote gave peres a chance to form a laborled coalition 
shamir the first premier to be turned out of office by a 
parliamentary vote in the history of the jewish state will remain 
as caretaker prime minister until a new government is seated 
peres won after shamir rejected a compromise offered by the 
ultraorthodox shas partys spiritual leader ovadia yosef who 
called for acceptance of us peace proposals for a 
palestinianisraeli dialogue five of the six lawmakers from shas 
then failed to attend the vote giving peres the margin of victory 
the compromise proposal was offered earlier today after more 
than five hours of angry debate in the 120seat parliament the 
debate was suspended to give the major political parties time to 
consider the compromise 
the us proposals would allow a deported palestinian and a 
resident of arab east jerusalem to serve on a palestinian 
negotating team that would meet with israelis in cairo 
shamir told parliament earlier today that the acceptance of 
arabs from east jerusalem in the peace process would compromise 
israels claim to sovereignty over the sector captured from jordan 
in 1967 
under the proposed compromise the two parties would have agreed 
that jerusalem is not negotiable and that it would remain united 
under israels rule shamir also would have reinstated labor 
ministers to the coalition in exchange for which the centrleft 
labor would drop its noconfidence motion 
before the noconfidence vote leaders of labor and likud both 
visited yosef to discuss the proposed compromise but to no avail 
when peres called for the noconfidence vote against shamir 
today he accused the rightwing leader of murdering the peace 
process 
shamir countered with an accusation that labor made repeated 
concessions to israels arab enemies calling this a shameful 
act 
the charge brought shouts of protest from labor ministers 
including peres who angrily wagged his finger at shamir and 
accused him of losing opportunities for peace 
i propose voting no confidence in the man who ended two 
processes peace and national unity peres said in a bitter 
speech 
shamir said he had been the driving force behind creation of the 
national unity government and that his party was just as interested 
in making peace as labor we are not afraid of peace or the peace 
process we fear irresponsible concessions shamir said calling 
for a defeat of the noconfidence motion 
shamir said the united states complicated the peace process by 
raising the sensitive issue of jerusalem and suggesting israels 
claim to the captured arab sector of the city should be a subject 
of negotiations 
there is only one jerusalem israels he said 
peres during his speech pointed a finger at shamir and accused 
him of breaking his commitment to religious and secular parties 
who will believe you again in this country you have broken every 
promise 
peres was interrupted frequently by likud heckling particularly 
from likud knesset member yehoshua matza who kept chanting 
subversive subversive 
a laborlikud coalition which has ruled israel through eight 
stormy years of repeated crises collapsed tuesday when shamir 
fired peres and the other 10 labor ministers resigned 
peres promised that a government led by his labor party would 
start peace talks with palestinians 
shamir said a victory by his likud bloc would delay if not 
cancel the israelipalestinian dialogue proposed by secretary of 
state james a baker iii 
