loan from the auction house which accepted the painting as 
collateral in an unusual transaction 
the highly leveraged acquisition similar to wall street 
takeover deals of whole corporations during the 1980s was widely 
criticized for inflating prices in the international art market 
the extraordinary prices paid for art in recent years also have 
placed many works beyond the acquisition budgets of art museums 
since bonds financial empire began crumbling under the weight 
of more than 5 billion in debt there has been widespread 
speculation among art curators dealers and collectors about the 
fate of irises 
the painting was in private european collections until 1947 
