a college freshman who fell to his death 
in a sport called elevator surfing was the latest casualty of a 
littleknown but dangerous practice that has plagued highrises for 
years officials say 
sometimes called elevator action or piloting an 
elevator the hazardous exercise involves climbing atop elevator 
cars either through a trapdoor in the cars roof or by jamming 
doors open from a floor above the car and riding on the roofs 
weve taken it terribly seriously weve been fighting it for 
a long time said val coleman director of public information for 
the new york city housing authority ten deaths and more than 50 
injuries have been reported in new york during the past five years 
he said 
its a very serious problem in our highrise buildings said 
coleman who worked on a recently released cautionary videotape on 
the issue called children are too young to die 
