mikhail s gorbachev granted a new more powerful 
presidency on thursday said his immediate tasks were to prevent 
the soviet union from breaking up and to promote freemarket 
reforms 
in assuming powers as the soviet unions first westernstyle 
president gorbachev warned in a speech at the congress of peoples 
deputies that the reforms required to right his countrys woeful 
economy would be painful 
mindful of his nations history of dictatorship and terror 
gorbachev promised legislators he would nurture the soviet unions 
young and not fully developed democracy 
gorbachev who ran into surprisingly strong opposition in the 
soviet congress before assuming the new presidency will now have 
wide powers to propose legislation negotiate treaties veto bills 
appoint the council of ministers and void its decisions 
significantly he also has the power to declare war if the 
country is attacked and under certain conditions impose direct 
presidential rule this means he could overrule a local government 
he has shifted his formidable powers further from the communist 
party leadership to the government on wednesday the congress 
struck the partys constitutional monopoly on power to permit 
development of a multiparty system 
gorbachev mentioned specifically the need to overcome the 
irresponsibility that was a byproduct of collective leadership 
saying an increase of responsibility is the main thing on which 
we rely 
he said in his speech at congress our country is living 
through difficult times but if we act together we will overcome 
the difficulties we must shake off fears and dejection gain a 
confidence in our strength and possibilities which are truly 
