<TEXT>
president bush may not believe in his lofty 
poll ratings but the democrats seem to and that is keeping them 
cautious or maybe timid 
thats a label they have tried to affix to bush who says the 
correct description of his style is prudent call it timidity or 
caution or prudence the tag applies on capitol hill as at the 
white house 
while democrats complain that bush is trying to avoid 
politically risky positions most of them are doing the same thing 
they just arent as visible with bush riding high in the 
popularity polls their challenges usually are safe rhetorical and 
standard 
