<TEXT>
in the auto industrys neverending search to 
find new ways of selling cars and trucks two makers are paying 
customers to do what comes naturally comparison shop 
nissan motor corp is offering 100 to anyone who test drives 
one of its stanza sedans but they only get the money if they end 
up buying a honda accord or toyota camry 
chrysler corp in february offered 50 to anyone who bought a 
car after testdriving a comparable chrysler product no matter 
what company made the vehicle 
the smartest shoppers could have pocketed 150 if they bought 
an accord or camry in the last two weeks of february and simply 
drove a stanza and a comparable chrysler product the nissan 
promotion began feb 12 and ends april 30 
the cash offers are the latest stunt in the ongoing trend of 
comparison advertisements in the auto industry automakers no 
longer use brand x in advertising they name names 
a federal trade commission rule change in the mid1970s allows 
direct comparisons if the claim is substantiated 
perhaps the bestknown comparison advertising battle on the auto 
scene is between chevrolet and ford trucks 
chevrolet aired a ditch of doom advertisement last year in 
which a chevrolet truck plowed through a muckfilled ditch 
shifting into fourwheeldrive while moving occupants of a ford 
truck had to stop get out and slog through the refuse to lock 
frontwheel hubs giving the truck fourwheeldrive capability to 
get through the trench 
chevrolets latest series dubbed ford county said 
chevrolet trucks outsold ford trucks in ford county ill that was 
just true enough for ford to seize on the claim 
ford acknowledged in ads that for a month or two chevrolet 
outsold ford in that county but for the previous 12 months ford 
said its trucks outsold chevrolet trucks nationwide including 
ford counties in several states and in chevy chase md 
along with the obvious goal of more sales comparison ad 
campaigns are designed to lure people into showrooms said jim 
wangers president of automotive marketing consultants inc in 
vista calif 
most of the retail people feel if i can get them in and get 
them on my grounds ill sell them wangers said thursday 
there is a percentage of the people who they can close in a 
sale if they can get them in 
chrysler and nissan dealers could use more traffic in their 
showrooms 
during the first two months of the year chryslers total 
vehicle sales of 305985 were down 14 percent compared with 
january and february last year and nissans total vehicle sales 
were 89974 off 163 percent 
the nissan offer works like this a potential buyer test drives 
a stanza between feb 12 and april 30 and fills out an evaluation 
form the dealer reviews it keeps one copy sends another to 
nissan headquarters and gives one to the consumer 
if the consumer takes delivery of an accord or camry within 
seven days of the stanza test drive and attaches the purchase order 
to the copy of the nissan evaluation the consumer gets the 100 by 
mail from nissan in four to six weeks 
if the consumer buys the stanza said nissan spokesman ec 
mueller theres no cash reward 
