francisco office to washington and on the same day wall had a 
telephone conversation with keating 
waxman outlined what she expected to be the result of the 
meeting including a new examination of lincoln and memorandum of 
understanding between the institution and regulators which was 
executed five days later 
san francisco is finished she assured keating thereis no 
going back to san francisco and nothing can be done to follow up 
their exam 
in the new exam she said nothing will be done that you 
are not aware of in advance 
also she told keating that bank board personnel will not be 
able to enforce any violation of the memorandum of understanding 
without going to the board first this will give you two 
bites at the apple before the board and in court if necessary 
the letter written in strong declarative language tracks 
with amazing accuracy the actions taken by the board actions 
which were interpreted publicly as clamping down on lincoln 
gonzalez said in reality as the letter carefully explains the 
actions were to be shams designed not to punish but to allow 
keating an escape route 
the letter indicates it was telecopied to keating in phoenix 
its existence was first disclosed in stories in thursdays editions 
of the san francisco chronicle 
its clear from the law firms memo that keating had undue 
and unprecedented influence on the board said rep jim leach of 
iowa a republican member of the banking panel this memo would 
appear to put wall at the center point of directing in a powerful 
if not coercive way his employees to abide by his decision to go 
easy on lincoln 
